Fix Applied:
1. Enhanced router reachability check in ServiceDeploymentValidator.php (line 270-284)
2. Now considers router available if EITHER:
   - Status is explicitly 'online', OR
   - VPN status is 'connected' AND last_seen within 5 minutes
3. Improved error message to show last_seen timestamp for debugging

Additional Tools:
- Created RetryRouterDiscovery command (app/Console/Commands/RetryRouterDiscovery.php)
- Usage: php artisan routers:retry-discovery --all
- Clears discovery locks and re-dispatches DiscoverRouterInterfacesJob
- Useful for routers stuck in pending after VPN connection succeeds

Changes:
- app/Services/ServiceDeploymentValidator.php: Enhanced reachability check
- app/Console/Commands/RetryRouterDiscovery.php: NEW - Manual discovery retry tool

Impact:
- Service deployment now works immediately after VPN connection
- No need to wait for interface discovery job to complete
- Better UX - router can be configured as soon as VPN is up
- Fallback validation prevents false "offline" errors

