2026-02-20T07:25:00Z | FIX | backend/app/Services/MikroTik/SshExecutor.php | Fixed wrong Router field names causing "Cannot connect to :. Error 0. Failed to parse address empty string": (1) host→vpn_ip??ip_address (explode CIDR), (2) ssh_port→port, (3) ssh_private_key→ssh_key with Crypt::decrypt() blob, (4) removed ssh_key_passphrase (no such field), (5) added timeout parameter to constructor (default 30s), (6) added Crypt facade import. Root cause: SshExecutor was using non-existent Router model fields. Root cause: namespace was App\Services\MikroTik but file lives in app/Services/ causing double autoload. Fixed: (1) namespace corrected to App\Services, (2) class renamed from MikroTikSshService to MikrotikSshService to match filename and all callers, (3) connect() updated to use correct Router model fields (vpn_ip/ip_address instead of host, ssh_key blob instead of ssh_private_key_path, PasswordEncryptionService::safeDecrypt for password), (4) added fetchInterfaces/fetchLiveData/executeCommand methods required by MikrotikProvisioningService and RouterController, (5) added parseInterfaces/parseSystemInfo/isConfigurableInterface helpers, (6) added Crypt facade import.
