2026-03-15 | ANALYSIS | Issue B re-diagnosed | Stacktrace confirmed useWritePdo() patch is running (visible in serialized closure) but still fails on Host 172.70.0.3:6432 (write PgBouncer). Root cause: PgBouncer is in TRANSACTION pooling mode. plain SET search_path is session-level; PgBouncer rotates backend connection between statements, so SET on stmt N is lost by stmt N+1. Fix: switch to SET LOCAL (transaction-scoped) + wrap all multi-statement tenant context callers in DB::transaction().
2026-03-15 | CHANGE | backend/app/Services/TenantContext.php | Changed all SET search_path to SET LOCAL search_path in setSearchPath() and clearTenant() for PgBouncer transaction pooling compatibility.
2026-03-15 | CHANGE | backend/app/Services/TenantContext.php | Wrapped runInTenantContext() and runInSystemContext() in DB::transaction() to hold single backend connection for duration of callback (required for SET LOCAL to persist across multiple statements).
2026-03-15 | CHANGE | backend/app/Services/MikroTik/RscFileCleanupService.php | Added DB facade import; wrapped queued closure body in DB::transaction() so setTenantById + Router::find execute on same backend PostgreSQL connection.
2026-03-15 | ACTION | backend/app/Services/TenantContext.php, RscFileCleanupService.php | Ran php -l validation (no syntax errors).
2026-03-15 | CHANGE | backend/app/Traits/TenantAwareJob.php | Applied same PgBouncer fix: replaced plain SET search_path with SET LOCAL inside DB::transaction() wrapper. Affects all queue jobs using TenantAwareJob trait.
2026-03-15 | ACTION | backend/app/Traits/TenantAwareJob.php, TenantContext.php | Final php -l validation passed (no syntax errors).
2026-03-15 | ANALYSIS | Root cause re-pinpointed | Production logs show 42P01 on Host 172.70.0.17 (read replica PgBouncer) for Router fetch and Host 172.70.0.3 (write PgBouncer) for Router insert. Both errors originate in SetTenantContext middleware: setTenant() issues SET LOCAL, then $next($request) is called OUTSIDE any transaction. PgBouncer returns backend to pool after SET LOCAL, so all controller queries see search_path=public. Fix: wrap $next($request) in DB::transaction() inside the middleware.
2026-03-15 | CHANGE | backend/app/Http/Middleware/SetTenantContext.php | Wrapped $next($request) in DB::transaction() when tenant context is set. This is the single correct fix point for all HTTP-path 42P01 errors: PgBouncer holds one backend connection for the entire request lifecycle within the transaction.
2026-03-15 | CHANGE | backend/app/Services/TenantContext.php | Removed DB::transaction() wrappers from runInTenantContext() and runInSystemContext(). These would cause nested SET LOCAL clearTenant() calls that reset search_path mid outer-transaction, breaking subsequent queries. Transaction responsibility delegated entirely to callers (SetTenantContext middleware, TenantAwareJob, RscFileCleanupService).
